Russian Grain-Crop Estimate Raised on Good Weather, SovEcon Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-27T13:08:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/russian-grain-crop-estimate-raised-on-good-weather-sovecon-says.html
  SovEcon  increased its estimate of
 Russia ’s grain crop to between 82 million and 86 million metric
tons on good sowing results and favorable weather, the Moscow-
based researcher’s Managing Director Andrey Sizov Jr. said.  The forecast was raised last week from a previous estimate
of between 80 million and 85 million tons, Sizov said today at a
Renaissance Capital investor conference in Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
